dcterms:description: DAVIS16 is currently the most popular VOS benchmark, consisting of 50 high-quality video sequences (30 videos for the train set and 20 for the val set). Each frame is densely annotated with pixel-wise ground truth for the foreground objects.
dcterms:title: DAVIS16

dcterms:creator: P. Ochs
J. Malik
T. Brox
dcterms:description: FBMS contains videos of multiple moving objects, providing test cases for multiple object segmentation. The FBMS has 59 sparsely annotated video sequences, with 30 sequences for validation.
dcterms:title: FBMS

dcterms:creator: F. Li
T. Kim
A. Humayun
D. Tsai
J. M. Rehg
dcterms:description: SegTrackV2 contains 14 densely annotated videos and 976 annotated frames. Each sequence contains 1-6 moving objects and presents challenges such as motion blur, appearance change, complex deformation, occlusion, slow motion, and interacting objects.
dcterms:title: SegTrackV2
